 At mean time, income is slightly more equal than earning in 2007.
 While there are obvious inequality in wealth.
 From the Lorenz Curve of wealth we can see that lowest 40% of the population
 have almost zero percent of total wealth and top 5% of the population have
 around 60% of total wealth in 2007.
 This result consists with the high number of top 1% / lowest 40% I obtained
